name: visitDeleteCommand
javadoc:
/**
 * Adds a delete command to be executed on the specified object.
 *
 * @param object The object that will be deleted.
 */
improved_javadoc:
/**
 * Adds a delete command to be executed on the specified object, marking it for deletion in the underlying data storage.
 *
 * @param object The object that will be marked for deletion.
 * @throws NullPointerException if the provided object is null.
 */

name: visitInsertCommand
javadoc:
/**
 * Adds an insertion command to be executed on the database.
 *
 * @param object The object that will be inserted into the database.
 */
improved_javadoc:
/**
 * Adds an insertion command to be executed on the database, persisting the specified object.
 *
 * @param object The entity or object that will be persisted and inserted into the database.
 * @return A unique identifier for the newly inserted object, if successful.
 * @throws NullPointerException If the provided object is null.
 */

name: visitKeepCommand
javadoc:
/**
 * Visits a keep command.
 *
 * If there are no pending deletions or insertions, increments the number of skipped commands.
 * Otherwise, handles the replacement and resets the pending collections.
 *
 * @param object the object to visit (not used in this implementation)
 */
improved_javadoc:
/**
 * Visits a keep command by checking if there are any pending deletions or insertions. 
 * If not, it increments the number of skipped commands. Otherwise, it handles the replacement and resets the pending collections.
 *
 * @param object the object to visit (not used in this implementation)
 */
